content.detailedDescription: I was driving down rainbow blvd heading north when from my drivers side window i saw this very bright orange glow. i had recently reported nine objects back on 12/13/07 and fortunately this time my wife was with me. i made a left turn into a parking lot and faced the car south where we were both able to see this orange glow.The glow faded to  a star like glow in the sky and we watched it standing still in the sky and then slowly move upward and in a southernly direction.It was different then the stars around it because it was orange in color.There was no shape other then starlike. i've spoke to ellen bullock,one of your investigators.She had interviewed me about the nine  incredible objects i saw in december and that's when i told her about this sighting.So we thought it was best to report this sighting also.Thank you
content.summary: Bright orange glow which faded to star like brightness hovered and slowly moved  up and in a southernly direction

content.detailedDescription: I was looking at the sky when these two silver looking objects appeared they were flying side by side just as they appeared both of them grew very bright then right before my eyes they just disappear
content.summary: Two silver objects appear grow bright then vanish

content.detailedDescription:
While returning home on street next to apartment(bout to pull in drive)
i happened to look up through driver window as i noticed what i thought to
be helicopter flying overhead. on closer look.. this was too large(to be
a helicopter), had 3 red lights forming a triangular shape, very 
dark(black)blocking out sky between its lights. quite large from as
best i could tell.

this object made absolutely no noise and looked to be floating
cross the city sky. the distance away from me was hard to judge, thus i
do not know size in relation to distance. it "felt" to be quite large based
on gut feeling. it moved slow but was moving. i really didn't think much
more about it other than "wow, that was strange".. and up till now, never
talked about it nor reported it. i did wonder if others had seen it and
just assumed if so.. it'd be in the paper the next day. i never did see
any articles or hear anything and just washed it away as an abnormal experience. 

 it was the silence of this object that truly was the most
eerie part of it.. and the fact that it was blocking out the sky with
it's blackness between its corner lights. the lights were not bright,
and i remember them being redish in color and defining the outer edges
of object(triangular).  

(this object was still passing overhead out of my view, but i didn't 
follow up on it - at the time, i had just put it out of mind as strange
event and went inside) i now carry a camera with me whenever driving.
content.summary: Triangular object(black)small light on each corner(3 total) floating silently in sky above

content.detailedDescription:
I was in my home and my family had just left home that night to go grocery shopping i walked them to the car and i happened to look up at the television tower as i live near the cable companies office and i noticed the usual red flashing light from the tower and 1 perfect circle a few feet above it it looked like it was at least 200- 300 feet from above it from my estimate and that circle had very very birght white light i ranto get the video camera and it was still there so i started filminig it and fromt he camera angle it looked like that circle was turning into 2 but i thought it was something to do with the camera lense so i look up without the camera and in fact that 1 bright circle of white light had turned into two objects tey made no noise and it just hovered in that same spot  when the other object appeared it was at the same altitude as the first but a few feet apart next to it. i don't know if someone taped over the video as i haven't seen that tape in years whic is a shame.


a few months later i did see some unidentified object this time i was walking in a school yard at about 5 or 6 in the afternoon this one was a fireball looking object it was bright flourecent orange and it was moving slowly at what i estimate was about 500 in the air it had a tail like a meteorite or a comet but i knew it was nothing like that because at the speed that it was moving i did not take pictures or video of this object as i had no camera with me at the time.

one thing i would want to mention is that i was aout 15 years old at the time of both sightings.
content.summary: 2 of my experiences

content.detailedDescription:
Have seen these lights now on the nights of january 19th, january 20th, & january 22nd. i really dont want to see them again.

i must also note that the area has an extreme amount of both red and white blinking radio/microwave antennas. also, seeing lights through the trees around here will give the illusion of blinking. there also is a fair concentration of oil & gas drilling rigs in the area. the following were not antennas nor was i observing them through trees... and i know for sure these werent drilling rigs. these objects look like planes at first, but under observation move and blink in an irregular fashion, unlike a plane. whatever they are, they scare the crap out of me. i am sure they will be up there again. but im not sticking around to get em on tape.

january 19th incident - roughly 8:30 pm
driving into mcalester, eastbound on 270
very high in the sky above mcalester i saw something streak across the sky at a high rate of speed. i grew up next to an airport, and this was too high to be traveling that fast. much too high. an airplane has lights flashing at a normal pulsing rate. this thing had both red and white blinking lights pulsing in a most irregular fashion. whatever it was, it was traveling north to south. the event took place in about 5-10 seconds total.

january 20th incident - roughly 9:00 pm
traveling eastbound on 270, between stuart and arpelar.
very high in the sky to the north, saw the same style of blinking red & white lights. the white lights seemed to blink in an irregular pulse in a circular pattern around the red light. the lights would disappear, and then reappear in the same spot in the sky. i put the pedal to the floor and did not look back or up.

january 22nd incident - roughly 9:00 to 9:40 pm
traveling from south of stuart, through stuart, and then eastbound through arpelar, then to mcalester.
was travelling north to stuart, ok. observed the same odd blinking irregular lights but much closer and much brighter, to the north. whatever was emitting them seemed to be on the ground to the north and west of stuart & 270 on top of a hill. if you were not observing it from on top of a hill, you would not of seen it from the highway. i was on a road south of the highway. also, to the south and west of stuart, for a brief moment there were the same type of lights observed just behind a hill there. i tried to get into the small town of stuart as fast as possible. once i got near stuart, i could no longer view either of these objects. i then turned east toward mcalester on 270. i looked up to the north, and noticed something moving in the sky. it kept its distance, but it looked like it moved faster almost to keep pace with me. this really scared me as i felt like i was under the objects observation. i was traveling the speed limit at 65 mph. i kept the object under my observation for roughly 15 miles. it just stayed in the same position in relation to my point of view. meaning, where i went, it went and stayed at a static distance from me. the lights blinked all kinds of weird directions. changing white to red to sometimes orange. also, the object moved vertically up and down whilst traveling horizontally. it would speed up and slow down. i can honestly say, i never wanted to see something like that and i hope i never see it again. once i made it into mcalester, i exited my vehicle and blinking lights caught my eye once again. just above the treetops, to the nne at a distance i can not discern, there appeared whitish orangish lights again. blinking strangely this time back and forth, back and forth. i observed this object for approximately 3 minutes before i had enough and locked myself inside.
content.summary: Strange lights in the sky

content.detailedDescription: On my way home from work traveling south from niagara falls ny towards buffalo, ny on a mostly clear sky where you can see for miles a light appeared from the east going towards the west.  i thought this to be odd because usually at that time of night i would see lights coming from the west going towards the east to the airport.  these are fairly odvious because they typically decend from the west towards the east and quite clearly an airplane.  but the light i saw that night traveled from the south east to the north west fairly quick almost like it was crashing.  it stopped like it hung in the air for about ten seconds and then departed to the south at a very rapid speed, disapearing in aproximatley 5 seconds.  when the object turned the lights where still as bright going towards the south as it was when it was heading north.
content.summary: Streaking across sky

content.detailedDescription:
Our house was in a very rural area on a hill 10 miles south of ironton and arcadia, missouri, on hwy e. it overlooked the road and a large flat field (larger than a football field and similarly shaped) across the road. one night when i was 9 or 10 years old i was looking out the window and saw two lights in the field. at first i thought people must be out there with lanterns on foot because the lights were moving a bit and were close to the ground. i watched them because i had never seen anyone in that field before, not even during the day. they started to move (independently) and i thought they were headlights of motorcycles. but then they moved impossibly fast all the way to the other side of the field. i think they were joined by a third and possibly fourth light. they seemed to be checking out the field and the perimeter of it. i believe they stayed close to the ground the entire time.

their speed is why i remember this at all, because i couldn't understand what could possibly move that fast, especially since there were no roads there or anything.

i went to get my parents to come see, but when we got back to the window, they were gone.

i don't remember the time of year or exact time of night, but we only lived there less than a year i think.  we moved out on april 1, 1970. we sold the 75 acre property later that year. i don't remember the address exactly, but you could find out by town records or i could probably find it.

when i heard last week about the sightings in texas, i was struck by the similarities.

the lights i saw were bright, white or yellowish-white lights, each like a single car headlight, though now that i think about it, from my vantage point it was hard to tell how big they were. they could have been bigger, but not a lot bigger.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Lights moving around a field impossibly fast, like recent ones in texas but 37 years ago

content.detailedDescription:
At least three of us watched in disbelief as the classic "flying saucer" made its way across the afternoon sky, heading east. altitude was about 300-500 feet. no sound at all. it appeared to have rotating white panels of lights, but the lights didn't move...The panels just sequentially lit in a rotating manner.

i was pumping gas at a gas station when i saw it...I ws just looking around at the trees. i asked the lady in her vw bug i was pumping gas into to get out of her car and tell me what that is. she said a flying saucer. so i ran into the gas station and got another attendant out there. same thing. flying saucer.

the ufo remained at the same altitude as it flew slowly and absolutely silently toward the east, we lost sight of it once it went behind some tall  trees. there was no audible or visible means of propulsion or lift (i am a pilot), and we were plent close enough (say 1500 feet) to hear it.

 about an hour later some friends came into the gas station. they were out on a golf course about 2 miles east of us. with no prompting from us, they blurted out that they had seen a flying saucer.

i was about 16 years old when this happened. i'm 48 today and remember it like it was yesterday. ever since then i've been a firm believer but have not seen another. the story about ufos in texas grabbed my attention and led me to this site. thanks for hosting it. its good to know that i (and for sure) we are not alone!
content.summary: Slow moving silver disk, rotating light

content.detailedDescription: On the night the lights were seen in stephenville, texas, my spouse mary rogers observed a low altitude fire ball traveling from the southeast headed northwesterly. i live approx 100 miles southeast of stephenville. my wife is a smoker and we do not smoke in the house, she was therefore sitting in the front yard in an auto smoking listening to the radio. when the object passed the signal from the radio station went dead. she states it lit up the sky brightly even before becoming visible, she exited the vehicle and observed what she describes a low altitude comet, or fireball with a tail passing overhead. she came inside and told me what she had observed and we dismissed untill the sighting reports the next day, the time of the event was not noted by us so it is strictly an estimate.
content.summary: Comet like fireball

content.detailedDescription:
We were coming home from the coleman pizza inn. we were driving a diesel jetta and were heading east on 1850 towards brownwood. we turned right onto 279 south and then turned left on park rd 15. during this time we saw an object in front of us through our windshield. it was amber in color. it appeared and disappeared about eight times, but it always appeared in the same location in front of us. when it appeared it would remain visible for about 30 seconds. i initially joked that a ufo was following us. but when the object remained with us, my wife became concerned. i wanted to stop the car and get out for a better look but my wife was too upset to allow me to stop. from park rd 15, we turned right onto county road 461. as we got close to county road 561, the object moved towards us and was directly above the car. it stayed above us for about 5 minutes. my wife thought it was about two telephone poles in height above the ground and i felt it was about 100 yards in diameter. it blocked out the stars. there were amber lights similar to a school bus around the perimeter of the circular object. underneath it were white lights that went off and on in sequence. the object appeared to be a dark metal but it was difficult to see the color of the metal at night. the object was totally silent. after about 5 minutes it began to slowly leave. it moved towards the northeast. as it left, it emitted sparkler like lights similar to what you see on the 4th of july. the sparklers were being emitted out of thin air near the object. they didn't seem to be coming directly from the object. it took it about 3 minutes to go out of sight.

this was the first ufo that we have ever seen. prior to this experience we were somewhat skeptical of people seeing ufos.
content.summary: Circular object about 100 yds in diameter

content.detailedDescription: Blocked out ski above us rt 100 west dover area..Then made loud grumbly woosh sound(didnt hear it when it was over our heads.We were in a truck heading towards north
content.summary: Dark triangular  red light on each tip

content.detailedDescription: My husband and i were watching tv on a sunday night in february 1991.We decided to shut the tv off and go to bed,it was around 10:30 pm.I was going to lock the doors and pull down the venecian blinds in the back room of the house,which has 4 large windows,when i noticed some very bright lights shining through the lats of the blinds of one window that had the blinds pulled half way down,so i said to my husband as i approached the window,"wow what the heck is that?" i put my face against the blinds to see what it was,so i peeked between the lats and said to my husband,"you should see how low this plane is!" so i pulled the blind all the way up so we could watch it.I was a little scared because it was too low and close.Then i noticed that it wasn't moving and that it had 3 very bright lights in a triangle pattern with one red pulsating light in the center of it.I thought it looked odd,because i had never seen a plane with that pattern of lights before and there was no green light on it like most planes have.We could not hear the engines either,so we went outside to listen to it,but it was silent.That freeked me out a little so my husband said,it's probably a helicopter.I told him that it was too close for us not to hear it.It was only like 300 feet away.So then i started to think that maybe it could be a ufo,but it wasn't shaped like a disk like most people say.I had never heard of triangle ufo's before.So then i wanted to get its attention,so i started flicking the back lights on and off,like in morse code and flashing a flashlight on and off towards it,then suddenly the craft's lights started coming towards my house.It freeked me out ,so i locked the doors and pulled down the blinds.We watched it for about 20 minutes or so,and then it suddenly,very slowly started to go towards the beach,until i could no longer see it.That was the first of 4 sightings.The second was in the middle of that same week,during the daytime,and the others were in 2007.My son told me that too many people don't report it,so i did my duty and eased my conscience after 18 years and hope others will do the same,so that we get more accurate statistics on ufo sightings.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change
content.summary: My husband and i saw  bright lights through my venecian blinds in the field behind my house

content.detailedDescription:
The witness was walking the dogs on the back nine of a golf course at this time. the golf course is the legends country club and is located in stephenville near prairie wind blvd. the sun had set and only a slight redness could be seen in its direction. he saw what looked to be two welding ark strikes at a distance of arms length and peas sized between my index finger and thumb. first one appeared and then another as the first bleeped out. they were like pearls on a string and looked like bubbles with a light encased inside. they were incredibly bright...Beyond halogen color temperature. just like an arc welding strike. there was no sound and they just trailed off to the west. they were traveling  just as a plane had passed and along the same trailing heading toward the southwest. they were probably 1 minute behind the plane and seemed to be moving at about the speed of a plane. they originated in the northeast and i saw them moving to the southwest towards dublin. they were around 25-45 degrees above the horizon.

he thought the lead plane might be a c-130 using a type of counter measure ordinance (as they use in iraq to confuse heat seeking shoulder fired rockets) but there were no point of source trails from the aircraft. they had to be at least ten miles down stream from the aircraft.

a week later on jan.15 or 16 at the same location, he saw two military jets flying in the same approximate path as the orbs that he had seen on jan. 8th.
content.summary: Two very bright orbs that took turns pulsating in brightness.

content.detailedDescription:
While photographing on starry night mode, 15 second exposure, i took pictures approx every 40 seconds. a few groups of 3 and other groups up to 9 shots  on tripod.

when reviewing the shots later, many well defined lights and objects were present on the camera. they were literally everywhere. some they were under the moon. others their three light formation was above the moon. third session lead stationary craft were much closer. many small objects way off in the distance, way beyond the moon. 

all small craft seemed to revolve around a huge green transparent orb with a scarlet red center. this kept working its way around the moon, almost appearing to wrap around it like a lens. guess this is where the eye of ra might have come from after filming this.

all shots are still but i have compiled two slideshow videos and posted on u2b. they can be found at www.Youtube.Com/dontspraymebro

i never saw the objects with my naked eye...Everything looked clear and normal.

actions were changing size and brightness, multipe "swapping" of bright colored light. no trails on the film which was set at 15 sec exposure, no contails and no light trail. from spot to spot instantly across what must be vast distances.

i feel very confident that these are not ours, not even our best could have been this fast, this organized, and this many.
content.summary: Photos of moon at night over sb. objects invisible. visible on leica d-lux3

content.detailedDescription:
On october 9th 2007, while standing in my driveway a friend and i noticed 4 very high altitude objects traveling very fast in a se to nw trajectory.  the time was approximately 4 pm and the sky clear and bright.  we noticed the objects about half way across the sky or directly overhead and by the time i ran to get my camera, they had moved across most of the remaining sky and were approaching the horizon.  eventually we lost sight at what i guestimate might have been several hundred miles out (i have no idea how far one can actually see on a clear day with an object that high in the atmosphere).  i'm guessing that the objects crossed the entire visible sky in 5-6 minutes or less.  while the four objects were traveling at approximately the same speed and in the same direction, there were some wild variations in flight.  the objects looked to be almost tumbling as they swerved back and forth, nearly impacting one another.  all four of the objects left a vapor trail and i have several pictures if anyone would like to take a look.  i have contacted nasa, local news agencies, local astronomy clubs, and an outfit called space-track.Org.  i have had no interest in the pictures and have been unable to find anything to suggest what it was we might have witnessed.  i originally thought that the objects might have been the breakup of a satellite or something along that line, but the space track page that claims to track all such occurances did not even show any items in a low decay orbit within days of our sighting.  the odd thing is that it appears that my freind and me may have been the only ones in our community who saw these objects.  i have two clean pictures if anyone would be interested.  they are fairly high resolution digital and you can zoom in for decent detail.  i would just like to know what it was that we saw.  

if web based gps visualizer is correct, the sighting was at approximately:
latitude 43.578595 
longitude -116.493492 

coordinates are:
n43���34.7157, w116���29.60952

i might be able to figure an approximate heading for the objects if that would be of use.
i am glad to share the pictures, but i retain right of ownership.
content.summary: Oct 9, 2007, 4 high altitude objects traveling erratically (tumblingh?) and very fast in same basic se to nw trajectory.

content.detailedDescription:
My girl friend and i were driving from the richland area towards union gap.  i dont live in that area so i'm not sure that there was a name for the location.  it was about 15 miles souteast of union gap on i-84.  there were few cars on the road and it is dark in that area.  roadside lights are kind of rare in that area as well.

i was driving and the girlfriend was the passenger.  i was looking at the roadway and into the distance (nw) when i noticed a very bright star and i thought to myself "i didn't see that before?".  it's brightness became more intense and larger.  it was at that point that i said to the girlfriend "look at that, do you see that?".  she said yes.

it went from a ever intensifying light into a suddenly present object.  i concluded that it had come from a great distance to nearby and that was accounting for its growing intensity.

i said "i'm gonna pull over" and i brought the car to a stop on the side of the road.  i turned off the headlights and then thought to myself "somebody is going to hit me if i don't have the lights on" and so i inadvertenly ended up flashing my headlights from on to off to bright to parking lights.

i got out of the car and noticed that the object went from a bright white light to several concentric circles of changing lights.  maybe three or four rows.  the lights changed colors from red to yellow and the object was having a visibly difficult time hovering in any one spot.  it would wobble and then seem to lose stability and then it would have to correct it self by using amazing bursts of speed from left to right and back again.

i thought to myself at the time "thats not very impressive, it cant even hover without trouble."  no helicopter could have stayed aloft with the stability issues this object was having and because of the sudden bursts of speed and the distance it was travelling in order to recover it was nearly immpossible that it was using rotors.

i noticed that a few cars had driven past and had not noticed but a car had pulled up behind us and the driver had exited his vehicle.  i looked at him and said "do you see that?" and he looked at at me and said yes as well as nodding.  i looked inside my car at the girlfriend and she was frozen and staring at the object.

the object continued to change colors and had periods of changing light intensity.  we stood and watched as the object made its way towards us and to our left (ne).  it began to descend about a quarter of a mile away and appeared to land just over the top of the hill to the north of our location.  it was still giving off light and at the point that it seemed to settle on the ground it looked like some kind of wavy beam was emitted from it that was kind of difficult to describe.

i looked back at the man who had stopped behind us and asked him if he was seeing this and he looked very scared and said yes.  i looked into the car at my girlfriend and at this point she was refusing to look at the object and was crying.  she was looking in the opposite direction and kept say "no,no" and crying. i took another look back at the other guy who was just stareing in the area of the object.  it had become dark again and he was just trying to see whatever it was.

i couldn't stand my girlfriends crying and began to think its time to get out of here. i got into the car and drove off while looking in the rearview mirror.  the other guy just kept standing there looking and watching.

i did my best to go over it with the girlfriend during the rest of our drive.  we were on our way to seattle at the time and it was about two more hours of me going over and over it.

i remember it so clearly.  it was difficult to judge the size of the object because it was dark and there were no visible objects on the ground for comparison or contrast.  i would have to say that it was about 80 feet acrossed.  using the lights that were on the bottom portion as reference i concluded that it was likely disc shaped.  i was amazed at how fast it originally approached from the western sky and how quickly it stopped.  most amazing was watching its hovering.  it was clearly unstable but could almost instantly dart from left to right at what was likely about a quarter of a mile (1100ft) to regain its stability.  i have gone over this in my head thousands of times trying to explain it away but it appeared an then landed and three of us watched it and agreed that we were seeing something that was solid or at least had the presence of mass.

i never reported it before because of the stigma attached to "kooks" who say they have seen something unexplainable.  with the recent texas sighting i noticed that the media has become a little less disrespectful of people who have made observations.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: It started as a bright light and then became an object that then landed

content.detailedDescription:
My wife and i were driving in far western dade county, west of homestead, in the rural areas where strawberries and tomatoes are grown, and a few remaining citrus trees.  we were looking at the last field, a 4 or 5 acre patch planted with strawberries, with a small house and barn towards the back, and beyond were the everglades, on the other side of a canal and a chain link fence.

we pulled to the side of the road to observe a bright light that was approachng silently from the wnw.  it was very, very bright.  it finally came to a stop and hovered over the farm house.  with a sharp hissing noise, a beam of light shone directly on the roof of the house for a few seconds, and then disappeared.  at this point, once our eyes had adjusted to the intense glare, we could se black spots (maybe windows?) along the widest point of the oval.

suddenly, there was a strange distortion developing in the sky over the house as the object became darker and appeared to shrink in on itself.  it was a kind of swirling distortion that appeared to increase in size and seemed even to distort the sunlight and clouds as it did, and the object became even darker and smaller.  then there was an audible, low-pitched popping sound, almost like one can make by pulling a finger out of one's puckered mouth, and the object disappeared altogether.  the distortion effect subsided, and then disappeared after a few seconds more.

we approached the house by passing through the gate and going up the driveway, and detected the strong smell of ozone, like from a stong electrical gadget, as well as an organic kind of repugnant stink.  we looked up at one of the windows and saw a grayish reptilian being staring at us.  we were so frightened, that we tore a u-turn right through a flower bed and drove away as fast as we could.

my wife begged me never to tell anyone about this, but i feel i must let the truth be known.
content.summary: Bright white glowing completely silent oval

content.detailedDescription:
Cleaning up a trailer in my trailer park located at 132 telegaph rd. plateau, al about 8:00 p.M. when me and my son looked outside and saw a orange glowing fireball about the size of a volkswagon  at tree top level coming down above the railroad located behind the trailer park and it was  making some kind of noise and i assumed it was a small helicopter on
fire.  it landed on the railroad track behind the trailer park and me and my son richard taylor jumped into my car (1963 cross-country rambler station wagon } to go around the woods between the trailer park and the railroad track to where we thought it went down.  however the car would not start and the battery was dead.  we tried several attempts to start
the car and each time the battery appeared dead and we could not start
the car...After about five minutes the glowing object arose up above the
railroad track and at about tree top level headed down the railroad track and once it crossed bay bridge viaduct on bay bridge rd. we tried to start the car again and was amazed when it started.  we drove out on
telegraph rd and went down about 2 blocks and turned left onto bay bridge
road and crossed cochran bridge and attempted to follow it until it went out over mobile bay at the bankhead tunnel, mobile, al..  shortly after about 4 or 5 heiicopters seemed to be pursing it, so we turned around
and proceeded back to the trailer park.......

i never reported it because i thought maybe people would think i was nuts....My car had never failed tocrank before and never did fail me again.....

the above story is the absolute truth and only now do i talk about it.
content.summary: Orange glowing object about the size of a volkswagon

content.detailedDescription:
My friend and i drove to ottawa the summer of 1972 or 73 for a weekend, looking for girls.  we ended up without any, sleeping in my car on the side of a highway.  we were awoken when a trooper stopped to check us out. when he left, we sat in the car eating some leftover bread.  the terrain was very flat with a mountainous area ahead in the distance.  we observed a disc-shaped object slowly moving across the flat field to our right, gradually approaching us.  it made no sound and came to a stop about 50 feet in the air and perhaps 200 feet in front of us over the highway.  it hovered there for around 10 minutes (i guess). i said to dave "you know what that is, right?" and he said "yup". no other words were spoken until the object was gone. there were colored lights that would appear across the side of the object and move along the surface. i wish i had had my camera along, for those would have been among the best photos ever taken.  the object then gradually moved directly away from us at an upward angle toward the mountain range then picked up speed rapidly until it was just a light in the sky, and made an instantaeous 90 degree turn to the left and zipped out of sight.

later that morning, when the radio stations began broadcasting, all they talked about were the hundreds of ufo sightings reported along the entire eastern seaboard from canada down through maine and into new england.  the official air force explanation reported about what we saw was "luminous gas from a factory". i know what i saw clearly that night, and it was a solid craft of some sort, not "luminous gas".

although i did not experience any fear during the event, i had recurring nightmares involving ufos and burning rays being shot from them (very thatrical) for many years, always the same helpless feeling.  i haven't had those dreams for decades now, but i think of the event often.  i located the friend who was with me about 20 years ago just to ask him if he still thinks about it and he indicated that he does not and cares no to.
content.flightPath: Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Silent ufo close to us, very good observation

content.detailedDescription: We (4 of us)were leaving the 9w bowling ally on route 9w it is set below the highway on the west side, so when pulling out onto 9w the car is inclined up so you are looking straight out the front windshield over the building on the other side of the road, the prentice hall building. there was a row of bright large rectangular windows with about a 2:1 hight to width ratio. at this time i was finishing my studies in aircraft design, so i tried to think of what it was that i saw. the only thing that came into mind was the gondola of a blimp. i don't recall why we couldn't see the shape, but i couldn't and was most fixed on the windows. we lowered the windows to see if we could hear the engines, but it was dead silent. we also could not determine as how far it was from us, so i drove the car across the highway to the left side of the prentice hall building while sticking our heads out and looking up to see if it would pass over us. it had been moving to the north an a crawling speed. we didn't see it pass over us and when we got into the prentice hall parking lot we got out of the car and looked in every direction and there was no sight of it. when i went to school, i asked a professor if blimps fly at night, and he said: no! when i got home, i called langley fields in nj where the blimps are, and they also told me the same thing. i've always wondered what we saw that night and when i came across this web site i started checking it out and found several similar reports in this area over the last 30+ years and one only a few blocks away on the same highway, and one a few miles away near the gw bridge.
content.summary: A row of bright rectangular windows with no visible exterior shape and dead silent, seen on 9w in englewood cliffs, nj

content.detailedDescription:
I wrote this story about an hour after the event. i mostly shared it with only my opened minded friends. the incident was somewhat disturbing to me and i kind of wanted to keep it to myself.  it happen in mcalister park san antonio on date a time noted on this form. resent incident in texas and san antonio have convinced me to share this story. i also view your organization as a creditable to properly investigate this base on resent news stories.I would like to retain my anonymity for now but will corporate with any investigate.

i was in my favorite park today and i went to look for the black stone i had thrown away there. when i reached the spot were i recalled throwing it i realized that the brush there was pretty thick. yet i had a strong urge to negotiate the brush and fine the stone. so i assumed the stone was calling me. as i found my way deep into the brush to the spot i felt i was being called to i began to look on the ground. i glanced up for a second a noticed what seemed to be an insect made purely of light. it flew directly in front of my face and paused as though it was trying to give me a better look.  i looked harder. ���jesus, jesus, jesus!!��� i said out loud. ���what is that?!��� i continued. then it suddenly occurred to me to ask it. ���what are you?��� i asked the little light thingy. ���i am a fairy,��� it replied telepathically. my thoughts and feelings where in an uproar. the thing began to fill my head with wisdom and information which at the time was clear but now seems vague. ���why are these things happening to me? i done completely lost my mind this time.  no one will ever believe this one.��� just then the light thingy spoke again, ���take a picture��� it said. as a pulled out my camera phone to take the picture it flew right up to the lens.  just then i saw that there were two of these things. as i watched the one on the right the other one flew off two the left. the one on the right disappeared. i looked to my left to see if the other one had disappeared also. it was no where to be found. ���here i am��� it said. i looked at a leaf on a tree and there it was. it looked like a small piece of lint or something so i blew on it. i didn���t move. i blew on it again. it didn���t move again. ���take another picture if you���d like��� it said. i did. i was about to place the leaf with the light thingy back in the tree when it said, ���i want to go with you���.  i switched the leaf with the fairy on it to my other hand in order to reach in my pocket to clear a space to carry it. my intention was to put this thing under a microscope and do a complete investigation. all on the sudden i felt a burning sensation on my hand with the leaf in it. the fairy had crawled on to my hand and it was burning me. my reflexes took control and tried to brush it away. i smashed it and it was spread across the palm of my hand. i had i feeling of great sadness come over me and was begging for forgiveness and understanding. the area on my hand where to thing was smashed was still burning. as i reached to wipe it off on my pants,��� it said, ���rub me on your skin around your heart���.  after i complied with its instructions it said, ���now you can take me with you���. 

update:  since this incident i have been compelled to pick up trash on the ground. i even pulled my car over one time and cleaned up the garbage that was thrown in a wooded area. today at the post office i picked up all the trash out front. i was just there to mail a letter.  i���m also finding the information given to me at the time can be recalled if i am asked the correct question.
i did not included this in the story but when you look at the picture please note that the dead leaf began to come to life as the being crawled up the leaf.
content.summary: Being made purely of light communicating by telepathy

content.detailedDescription:
Was awakened @ approximately 3am while sleeping on tv room couch by our television and lights acting eratically.  there was a strange hum coming from the plasma television...Far louder than usual start-up hum you would associate with that kind of electronics.  

got up and started upstairs to get a flashlight, because i believed we were having electrical issues and the power was about to go out.  upon reaching the top of the stairs i was greeted by a strange green-blue light that was flashing outside.   it looked to be originating to the south of us (the windows i was looking out were on the north side) and in the general direction of fredericton, but the flash covered the entire sky for about 4 seconds and only slowly oscillated in color and intensity.  it was at this time that our house lights flickered and dimmed and then went out...While our neighbors lights across the street and to each side of us, stayed on.  strange.  i'd place the time of this happening no later than 3:05 atlantic.

by this time, the wife was up, asking if i'd seen what she had from the bedroom and we both commented on the strange quality of the light and the strange effects (apparent electrical interference, etc).  our lights came back on after a couple of minutes and i walked outside to see if anything had happened to our power line coming off the local pole or at its contact point at the side of the house.  no issues.  there was a moderately high wind, but none of the lines were moving more than normal and no trees or branches are close to our lines.

i'd place the time by now at 3:15-3:18.  the power now went off along the entire block.  looking across the ridge from our location we could tell that the entire area was impacted.  by 3:20-ish i noted the sound of a large 4 engined aircraft orbiting above the cloud cover and believe it was a c-130 hercules dispatched out of cfb gagetown, a relatively short distance away. large aircraft are not known to transit over our area, much less linger.  puddle jumpers yes, large multi-engines are rare.  another 'out of the ordinary' for this early morning.  thinking that we may have had a tree across the lines, i got in the truck to find the location so we could report it to nb power.  no sooner had i gotten to the bottom of the hill (about 3:35 am) than i came face to face with an nb power panel truck sitting by the side of the road.  my first thought was 'wow, that's extreemly fast reaction to trouble calls'...My second thought was 'there was no way anyone could have reacted that fast to a recent call.'  regardless, he was johnny on the spot with his trucks yellow light flashing, parked at the intersection of mccleod hill rd and hillview dr.  

as it was still dark and there was someone on the scene, i went back home and waited for daybreak to see what was what.  a trouble call put into nb power was answered by the automated system and gave 3:18 as the most recent other call in the area...Problem unknown.  a later call @ 5:00 am gave the most recent report as 4:20 with the explaination 'trees down on lines' and an estimated time of repair, which i fail to recall.  

just after 7:30 am there was enough light to begin poking around and so i did.  the two breaks in the power lines closest to us were at the corner of mccleod hill rd and hillview dr. and about 1/4 of a mile to the nnw on mccleod hill rd.  at both locations the only line impacted was the center line of three power lines, and the break of line occured dead center between power poles.  the areas where the breaks occured were well cut back at one location, with no evidence of live or dead fall in the area of the break - and cut well below the level of the power lines in the other break area...Again with no branches or trees down.  as stated, only the center lines were impacted and were spliced/bridged in short order.

more than that cannot be relayed, due to cloud cover.  it should be mentioned that no local transformers were tripped during the incident and no lightning was reported that night.  furthermore, it was strange in that most of our neighbors were awakened by the light and that it was a strange enough occurence to merit discussion across the community about our 'little green visitors'.  evidently, few others thought it was lightning.

shortly after the incident occured, nb power took down 3 complete grids, affecting more than 1100 homes in the area, on the pretext that there was only a single power control point to deactivate in order to facilitate repairs...And this long before any crews would have responded.  and no trees across the lines (at least in our area).  curious and leaves me wishing it was a clear night!

photos were taken of the repair areas, showing the splices done by the crews and the ground under and around the breaks.  they can be provided, but do not show the crews in action, or any great detail.  the only thing they show is no material of any sort impacting the lines.  

finally, being ex-military, i am well aware that there is powerful aew equipment on modified hercules and other large aircraft that can easily disrupt local power if 'lit-off' by accident. however, i'd be inclined to think that any kind of surge from that equipment would have messed with transformers as well... 

that's all i have to report.  come to your own conclusions, and if you're a 'local' you can now rest assured that 'yes...Someone else saw what you saw.'
content.summary: Possible ufo and high energy discharge above cloud cover

content.detailedDescription:
I was driving to work on interstate 84 west and i was on the mountain and to my right i could see this strange light.  i tried to see if it was an airplane and it was none that i have ever seen.  it was all glittering light, it looked like 3 bright diamonds in the sky.  i made sure to look at the time on my clock just in case anyone reported it.  the area i saw it in was very clear, not many clouds and it was a morning blueish sky, not a night sky. this is a famous look out point where you have an amazing view.  there were people who were stop at this truck/rest stop.  you can see three states. ny nj pa.  i did not stop because i had to be at work at 7 a.M.

i did not say anything to anybody. it was a very busy day at the hospital.

the next day i was working with a different nurse and she mentioned to me that she saw a ufo yesterday.  i was like you got to be kidding me.  she describe it in much more detail.  she was coming from sullivan county and may have been closer to it.  she said it changed colors and was oval or circular.  i then told her you will not believe this but i saw something strange when driving to work.   she then told me she was also driving to work around the same time of day.

i called our local newspaper and left a message.  they did not call back.
i called the port jervis police dept and asked if anyone had reported something strange in the sky and he said no.  i told him there was someing in the sky early on the morning of the 19th and that was that.
i called the same lousy newspaper again and they put me through to some reporters voice mail and i did not get a call back.  what a suprise.

in my 38 years i have never seen anything strange or unidentifiable in the sky.  nobody cares.  who knows what it was but i would think it would be important for national security.
content.summary: Looked like 3 bright lights in the sky, beautiful start like glow, too close to be stars

content.detailedDescription:
This was a broad daylight sighting from our home on the outskirts of hamilton, texas. hamilton is located in the center of hamilton county adjacent to stephenville texas. this object was traveling from south to north toward stephenville/chalk mountain. we are approx. 40 miles south of stephenville. i was out in the middle of the yard with our dogs at approx. 9 a.M. on a clear, cloudless day with unlimited and unobstructed visibility. i was alerted to look up by our labrador bird dog frantically barking at the sky. there were no wings, no contrail, and no noise associated with this event. it appeared to be very high and very huge. it would have taken a silver dollar at arms length to cover the object from fore to aft. it was traveling s. to n. at what appeared, from my perspective, a slow rate of flight. i first observed it at about the 10:00 position off the southern horizon and observed it to approx. the 2:00 position. total elapse time was approx. 45 seconds. i took my eyes off just long enough to shush the barking dog and when i looked back up... it had just disappeared. other than our dogs, i personally know of no other witnesses to this event. in fact, i would be very interested to know and compare notes/thoughts with any other observers. 

this was definitely not a helicopter, airplane, blimp, baloon, bird, etc.
although hamilton airport has no radar capabilities, ft. hood @ killeen and waco regional airport should have seen something. lots of luck on getting anything from the military. (sketch attached).

i seek no notoriety, publicity, remuneration, ......No nothing. in fact, i demand privacy and confidentiality. i have a low tolerance and much disdain for rednecks & idiots who refuse to accept reality and admit the truth.

jayne chambliss
content.summary: Ufo daylight sighting over hamilton, texas (see attachment)
